“You mean that great possessions warm the cockles o your heart,” I said;
                        “that's because you're all soul. As for me, I must warm my hands in the
                        tea-cozy before I can carve the eggs.”

“Oh no!” said the prettiest girl, “only to make us look like learned
                        antiquities—antiquaries, I mean. It was an awful bother collecting them all;
                        some of them have no glass in.”
